June 2022

Thrilled for OPLSS this year! I am grateful for the opportunity to learn more about programming lanugages at OPLSS and for their support towards my travel.


April 2022

Awarded the NSF Graduate Research Fellowship! Great thanks to my letter writers, advisors, and professors both at CMU and KU who have supported my growth. It takes a village.

Thankful for the opportunity to attend CRA-WP Grad Cohort this year! I networked with many brilliant and passionate computer scientists and gained insightful advice from industry and academic mentors.


January 2022

So grateful to have been awarded support to attend POPL PLMW this year! I learned a lot from the talks and received great advice. One of my favorite bits of wisdom is "research is a conversation".


December 2021

Woohoo, our team placed 2nd in the LFCPS Grand Prix! Special thanks to Andr'e\u00E9' Platzer for a great semester and to all the industry judges who came to hear about our project. Excited about our work on identifying modeling errors in dL formulas! \u1F483


October 2021

It's a girl! Thrilled to be co-advised by Jan Hoffmann and Limin Jia. I am so excited for all that I will learn!


August 2021

"We're not in Kansas anymore", said a very confused Dorothy to an even more confused Toto. Same here (but less confused). Just moved to Pittsburgh, and I am thrilled to start grad school at Carnegie Mellon this fall! (no flying monkeys yet, but I'll let you know of any sightings.)


July 2021

Published website. Hello world :)
